docs.abstract: President Trump often tries to spin resignations as firings, a reaction driven by a hypersensitivity to the perception that anyone would ever want to leave him.

docs.lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — In an interview on Monday on “Good Morning America,” Cliff Sims, a former White House aide promoting a tell-all book about life inside the West Wing, wanted to make clear that he had left his job on his own terms. Anticipating pushback from the White House, he told George Stephanopoulos, the host, that he had brought his resignation letter along to prove it.

headline.main: The Many Ways to Leave the White House
headline.print_headline: A Dizzying Turnover And Predictable Spin

docs.lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — President Trump has insisted that he is not going to compromise with Democrats to end the government shutdown, and that he is comfortable in his unbendable position. But privately, it’s sometimes a different story.

docs.lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — Aleksej Gubarev is a Russian technology entrepreneur who runs companies in Europe and the United States that provide cut-rate internet service.
